-- South Korea Household Income Rises for 10th Straight Quarter
-- B y   E u n k y u n g   S e o
-- 2012-05-18T03:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-18/south-korea-household-income-rises-for-10th-straight-quarter.html
South Korean household income rose
for a 10th straight quarter from a year earlier as employers
added more full-time jobs.  Average monthly income at households gained 6.9 percent to
4.1 million won ($3,495) in the first quarter from a year
earlier after a 7.3 percent gain in the previous three months,
Statistics Korea said in a report today.  Household monthly spending excluding tax and social
security-related payments increased 5.3 percent to 2.6 million
won last quarter from a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eunkyung Seo in Seoul at 
